The number of confirmed cases in South Africa is 2,272 and two more deaths. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There are 99 new coronavirus infections in South Africa. This brings the total number of 2,272 infections in the country. Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize also revealed that two more people have died bringing the number of fatalities to 27. Meanwhile, more than 1.8 million people have been reported to be infected by the novel coronavirus globally and 115,242 have died, according to a Reuters tally. READ: North West doctor tests positive for COVID-19 Infections have been reported in more than 210 countries and territories since the first cases were identified in China in December 2019. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. - Additional reporting by Reuters